Italian Stocks: UniCredit, Banca Monte dei Paschi Move in Milan

-- B y   G i l e s   B r o o m
-- 
2011-02-15T16:57:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/italian-stocks-mediaset-unicredit-banca-monte-dei-paschi-move.html
Italy’s benchmark  FTSE MIB Index 
increased 186.53, or 0.8 percent, to 22,823.82 at the 5:30 p.m.
close in Milan, the highest level in nearly 10 months.  The following stocks were among the most active in the
Italian market today.  Banca Monte dei Paschi di Siena SpA (BMPS IM) surged 5.4
percent to 97.9 euro cents, the highest price since November. A
gauge of European banks rose 1.3 percent after London-based
Barclays Plc reported better-than-estimated full-year net
income. Unione di Banche Italiane ScpA (UBI IM) gained 2.5
percent to 7.51 euros.    Parmalat SpA  (PLT IM), Italy’s largest dairy company, fell
3.2 percent to 2.17 euros, its biggest drop since July, after
news agency Ansa reported that the government may introduce
legislation limiting its dividend payment to 50 percent of
earnings.    UniCredit SpA  (UCG IM) surged 3.3 percent to 1.91 euros
after Societe Generale SA upgraded the Milan-based bank to
“buy” from “sell.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Giles Broom in Zurich at 
 gbroom@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Merritt at   dmerritt1@bloomberg.net . 